            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Closer adjustment can be made by sanding next thicker spacer to desired thickness using emery
                        cloth on a flat surface.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Wash spacer thoroughly of emery cuttings before installing on pinion.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After proper preload is achieved, remove end yoke and install a new seal. Apply a small
                    amount of light grease on lip of sealing surface prior to installation (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400843">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400843" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400843" filename="../figg14/G1400843.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 43. Apply Grease</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and dry threads on pinion. Install end yoke, washer, and new prevailing torque
                    pinion nut. Use a torque multiplier wrench and tighten nut to 900 to 1200 ft-lbs. (1220 to 1,627 N&#8226;m)
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400844">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
                </para>
